 emphasizing the importance of strengthening international law and increasing the authority of multilateral institutions, such as the United Nations. The book includes a foreword by Mikhail Gorbachev, an Introduction by Jonathan Schell, and response essays by Jane Goodall and Jonathan Granoff.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 31. Jan 2022) 7aPOLITICAL SCIENCE / General.2bisacsh1 aCranston, Alan, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aCranston, Kim, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aGoodall, Jane, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGorbachev, Mikhail S., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGranoff, Jonathan, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aSchell, Jonathan, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb40uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978080476747740uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780804767477423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780804767477/original  aGBV-deGruyter-alles